# =============================================================================
# .gitignore — examples/lfd-system-verifier (project-local)
# =============================================================================
# The verifier-project is part of the LFD bundle, but everything
# it generates at runtime is EPHEMERAL and regenerated by every
# run. None of the per-run outputs (reports, logs, scratch dirs,
# snapshots) belong in the repo. The committed tree contains
# only the verifier code itself (scripts, prompts, graders,
# README, GOAL, AGENTS, .gitignore). To see what a verifier
# run produced, run ./run-verification.sh or
# ./run-verification-real.sh and inspect the outputs locally.
# =============================================================================

# ----- top-level ephemeral outputs (regenerated every run) -----

# Both verifiers write a markdown + JSON report at the
# verifier-project root. These are the "what was tested"
# artifacts for the most recent run.
verification-report.md
verification-report.json
verification-report-real.md
verification-report-real.json

# Per-cycle loop state. cycle-1/, cycle-2/, etc. are
# created by the loop driver; .iterations/ holds the
# wrapper's per-cycle directory; .loop_start_ts tracks
# the wall-clock budget.
logs/cycle-*/
logs/.loop_start_ts
logs/iteration-log.md
logs/best-cycle.json
logs/held-out.log
logs/held-out-score.json

# Score snapshots (the report reads from these instead
# of the live cycle dir, since the live dir gets wiped
# by cleanup before the report phase).
logs/design-set-score.snapshot.json
logs/real-design-set-score.snapshot.json
logs/sub-losses.snapshot.json

# Token / duration tracking (used by the loop's budget
# instruments; not part of the committed tree)
logs/tokens_used.txt
logs/tokens_last_cycle.txt

# ----- per-task scratch logs (regenerated every run) -----

logs/*

# ----- per-iteration workspace -----

# The loop driver creates .iterations/cycle-N/<task>/ under
# the project root for each cycle's wrapper scratch dir.
.iterations/

# ----- runtime-generated files (not source) -----

# The loop-driver symlink is created at runtime by
# run-verification.sh. It points at the canonical loop-driver
# in the parent repo's skills/ directory, so committing it
# would create a circular reference.
loop-driver

# The copied sub-loss scorer is regenerated by the
# orchestrators from the canonical source at
# cline-orchestration/references/compute-sub-losses.py.
verifiers/compute_sub_losses.py

# Parser scratch (from earlier d1 testing — leftover state
# from when d1's grader inlined a parser; no longer used)
test-tasks/parser-out.json
test-tasks/parser.err
